# Tor configuration for the Jumpcoin wallet container.
#
# This file is only used in the WITH_TOR=true image variant (the
# :tor tag).  Supervisord starts /usr/bin/tor with this config.
#
# Listening on 127.0.0.1 keeps the proxy inside the container; the
# wallet reaches it at SOCKS5://127.0.0.1:9050.
#
# We do NOT set "User" here because supervisord itself runs as the
# unprivileged jumpcoin user (see docker/entrypoint.sh and
# supervisord.conf).  Instead, supervisord's [program:tor] block
# sets user=debian-tor so tor drops to that account at start.

SocksPort 127.0.0.1:9050 IsolateClientProtocol IsolateClientAddr
ControlPort 127.0.0.1:9051
CookieAuthentication 1
# Jumpcoin runs as the unprivileged "jumpcoin" user.  The Tor image adds that
# user to the debian-tor group so it can authenticate to the control port and
# create its v3 onion service automatically.
CookieAuthFile /var/lib/tor/control_auth_cookie
CookieAuthFileGroupReadable 1
DataDirectory /var/lib/tor
DataDirectoryGroupReadable 1

# Avoid log noise on stdout (we already have supervisor capturing
# the process); uncomment for debugging.
# Log notice stdout
